### dotnet-orders demo - a multi-step cart checkout.
### Open in VS Code (REST Client extension), Visual Studio, or Rider's HTTP client
### and run each request with the "Send Request" / play button, top to bottom.
###
### Each step hands you an id that the next step needs, and you copy-paste it in by
### hand: cartId, then itemId, then orderId. That drudgery - and the off-by-one
### "oops, wrong id" mistakes - is exactly what proxymock's Smart Replace
### ("Correlated ID") recommendations remove when you record this flow.

@host = http://localhost:8082
# Recording with proxymock (`make record`)? point at the recorder instead:
# @host = http://localhost:4143

### 1 - Start a cart and add an item. Note BOTH the cartId and itemId in the response.
POST {{host}}/carts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "WIDGET-1",
  "qty": 2
}

### 2 - Bump the quantity. Paste the cartId AND the itemId from step 1 (two pastes).
POST {{host}}/carts/items/update
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cartId": "paste-cartId-from-step-1",
  "itemId": "paste-itemId-from-step-1",
  "qty": 5
}

### 3 - Checkout the cart. Paste the cartId again. The response has a new orderId.
POST {{host}}/carts/checkout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cartId": "paste-cartId-from-step-1"
}

### 4 - Confirm/pay the order. Paste the orderId from step 3.
POST {{host}}/orders/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "paste-orderId-from-step-3"
}

### 5 - (optional) List orders
GET {{host}}/orders
